SIMPLE: interim
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interim
<hw>In"ter*im</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>inter</ets> between + <ets>im</ets>, an old accusative of
<ets>is</ets> he, this, that.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The meantime; time intervening; interval between
events, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the <qex>interim</qex> is⟦br⟧
Like a phantasms, or a hideous dream.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Hist.)</fld> <def>A name given to each of three
compromises made by the emperor Charles V. of Germany for the sake of
harmonizing the connecting opinions of Protestants and
Catholics.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interior</ent>⟦br⟧
